TASK-4
Investigate the relationship between the age of farm tractors and their maintenance costs using data collected from Putnam County, FL.
Data Points:
Tractor Age (5,10,15,20,25)
Maintenance Costs (600,1400,1400,1200,800)
Data Characteristics:
Maintenance costs peak at mid-life (15 years).
Costs reduce after the mid-life stage.

Model Used:
Polynomial Regression (2nd Degree),4th degree and spline

Observation points:
Maintenance costs are highest at around 15 years of tractor age.
Younger tractors have relatively lower costs.
Older tractors beyond 20 years also show declining maintenance costs.
